# Secrets — key-per-file layout
#
# In production, the Azure Key Vault CSI driver mounts each secret as its own
# tmpfs file at /mnt/secrets-store (one file per secret: file name = key, file
# contents = value). The app reads them key-per-file (secrets/secrets.go) — the
# Go equivalent of .NET's AddKeyPerFile. No secret is ever stored in this repo,
# the image, config files, a Kubernetes Secret, or an env var.
#
# For local development, run ./start/setup-secrets.sh to create the same layout
# under $HOME/.pellerex/secrets/RepoUniqueNormalisedIdentifier and export
# SECRETS_MOUNT_PATH to point at it. The recognised keys are:
#
#   APISecretKey         e.g. your-secret-key-here-change-in-production
#   Environment          e.g. development
#   DbConnectionString   e.g. Server=localhost;Database=...;User Id=sa;Password=...;TrustServerCertificate=True;
